<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a1ebd16-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s3614"><num value="3614">§ 3614.</num><heading> Waiver of rights as void</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any condition, stipulation, or provision binding any person to waive compliance with any provisions of this chapter shall be void.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a1ebd17-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/399/tVI/s615">Pub. L. 96–399, title VI, § 615</ref>, <date date="1980-10-08">Oct. 8, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/1680">94 Stat. 1680</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
